<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Barcelona manager Ronald Koeman has revealed that there are no issues between himself and Lionel Messi following this summer's transfer saga.</p>

<p>The Argentine superstar told Barcelona, via fax, he wanted to leave the Nou Camp this summer but performed a dramatic U-turn by announcing he would stay at the club this season.</p>

<p>Koeman, who was appointed manager in August following the dismissal of Quique Setien, has shed light on on the story that dominated football and his relationship with the club's star man.</p>

<p>Ronald Koeman has revealed that there are no issues between himself and Lionel Messi </p>

<p>'That has passed me reasonably well,' he told Fox Sports.</p>

<p>'That was mainly a conflict between Messi and the club. </p>

<p>'I have spoken to Messi since then and we will continue as usual.'</p>
